import sys
import subprocess
import os
import platform
import importlib
import urllib.request
import time

TARGET_PY_VERSION = "3.10"
ENV_NAME = "ml_env"

PAQUETES = {
    "pymongo": "pymongo",
    "pandas": "pandas",
    "numpy": "numpy",
    "scikit-learn": "sklearn",
    "lightgbm": "lightgbm",
    "optuna": "optuna",
    "joblib": "joblib",
    "matplotlib": "matplotlib",
    "seaborn": "seaborn",
    "tensorflow": "tensorflow",
    "keras": "keras",
    "imbalanced-learn": "imblearn"
}

def run(cmd):
    print(f"\n$ {' '.join(cmd)}")
    return subprocess.check_call(cmd)

def python_version_ok():
    major, minor = sys.version_info[:2]
    return (major == 3 and minor <= 11)

def download_python310():
    print("\n Descargando Python 3.10")

    installer_url = "https://www.python.org/ftp/python/3.10.11/python-3.10.11-amd64.exe"
    installer_path = "python310_installer.exe"

    urllib.request.urlretrieve(installer_url, installer_path)
    print(" Instalador descargado.")

    print("\n Instalando Python 3.10 en modo silencioso")

    cmd = [
        installer_path,
        "/quiet",
        "InstallAllUsers=1",
        "PrependPath=1",
        "Include_launcher=1"
    ]

    run(cmd)
    print(" Instalacin completada.")

    # esperar un momento para que el sistema actualice las rutas
    time.sleep(5)

def find_python310():
    candidates = ["python3.10", "py -3.10", "python310", "python3"]

    for c in candidates:
        try:
            run(c.split() + ["--version"])
            return c
        except:
            continue

    return None

def create_environment():
    print(f"\n Python {sys.version.split()[0]} incompatible con TensorFlow.")
    print(f"Buscando Python {TARGET_PY_VERSION}\n")

    python_exe = find_python310()

    if python_exe is None:
        print(" Python 3.10 no encontrado.")
        download_python310()
        python_exe = find_python310()

        if python_exe is None:
            raise RuntimeError("No se pudo instalar ni encontrar Python 3.10.")

    print(f"\n Usando {python_exe} para crear el environment.")

    run(python_exe.split() + ["-m", "venv", ENV_NAME])
    print(f"\n Environment '{ENV_NAME}' creado.\n")

def get_env_python():
    if platform.system() == "Windows":
        return os.path.join(ENV_NAME, "Scripts", "python.exe")
    else:
        return os.path.join(ENV_NAME, "bin", "python")

def instalar_paquetes(python_exec):
    print("\n Instalando paquetes requeridos\n")

    for paquete, nombre_import in PAQUETES.items():
        print(f" Verificando {paquete}")

        try:
            subprocess.check_call(
                [python_exec, "-c", f"import {nombre_import}"],
                stdout=subprocess.DEVNULL,
                stderr=subprocess.DEVNULL
            )
            print(f"   {paquete} ya est instalado.")
            continue
        except:
            print(f"   {paquete} no est instalado. Instalando")

        try:
            run([python_exec, "-m", "pip", "install", paquete])
        except Exception as e:
            print(f"   Error instalando {paquete}: {e}")

def main():
    if python_version_ok():
        print(f" Python {sys.version.split()[0]} es compatible.")
        python_exec = sys.executable
    else:
        print(f" Python {sys.version.split()[0]} NO es compatible con TensorFlow.")
        create_environment()
        python_exec = get_env_python()

    run([python_exec, "-m", "pip", "install", "--upgrade", "pip"])
    instalar_paquetes(python_exec)

    print("\n PROCESO COMPLETO")
    print("\nPara activar el environment usa:\n")
    if platform.system() == "Windows":
        print(f"    {ENV_NAME}\\Scripts\\activate")
    else:
        print(f"    source {ENV_NAME}/bin/activate")

if __name__ == "__main__":
    main()

    # ---- cargar DataFrame desde Mongo ----
    df = pd.DataFrame(list(col.find({}, {"_id":0})))
    print("DataFrame cargado con shape:", df.shape)

    # ---- Aplanar columnas anidadas ----
    nested_cols = ["demographics", "financial_profile", "credit_behavior", "loan_request", "ratios"]

    for nested in nested_cols:
        if nested in df.columns:
            print(f"Aplanando columna: {nested}")

            # Convertir valores en dict (si algo no es dict, meter dict vaco)
            safe_dicts = [
                x if isinstance(x, dict) else {}
                for x in df[nested]
            ]

            # Expandir a DataFrame
            expanded = pd.json_normalize(safe_dicts)

            # Renombrar con prefijo
            expanded.columns = [f"{nested}_{c}" for c in expanded.columns]

            # Reemplazar columna original por las expandidas
            df = pd.concat([df.drop(columns=[nested]), expanded], axis=1)

    print("\nAplanado completado.")
    print("Columnas finales:")
    print(df.columns.tolist())
    print("Nuevo shape:", df.shape)

(8) Utilities: mtricas y graficado (usaremos plasma)

Code 
import math
from sklearn.metrics import roc_auc_score, precision_recall_curve, auc

def evaluate_model(clf, Xt, yt, name="model"):
    y_proba = None
    try:
        y_proba = clf.predict_proba(Xt)[:,1]
    except:
        # si no tiene predict_proba
        y_proba = clf.predict(Xt)
    y_pred = (y_proba >= 0.5).astype(int)
    acc = accuracy_score(yt, y_pred)
    f1 = f1_score(yt, y_pred)
    roc = roc_auc_score(yt, y_proba)
    return {"name": name, "accuracy": acc, "f1": f1, "roc_auc": roc, "y_pred": y_pred, "y_proba": y_proba}

def plot_roc(y_true, y_proba, title="ROC Curve"):
    fpr, tpr, _ = roc_curve(y_true, y_proba)
    plt.figure(figsize=(6,4))
    plt.plot(fpr, tpr, label=f"AUC = {auc(fpr,tpr):.3f}")
    plt.plot([0,1],[0,1],'--', alpha=0.6)
    plt.xlabel("False Positive Rate")
    plt.ylabel("True Positive Rate")
    plt.title(title)
    plt.legend()
    plt.grid(True)
    plt.show()

(9) Optuna objective - RandomForest

Code 
def rf_objective(trial):
    params = {
        'n_estimators': trial.suggest_int('n_estimators', 50, 400),
        'max_depth': trial.suggest_int('max_depth', 3, 20),
        'min_samples_split': trial.suggest_int('min_samples_split', 2, 20),
        'min_samples_leaf': trial.suggest_int('min_samples_leaf', 1, 20),
        'criterion': trial.suggest_categorical('criterion', ['gini','entropy']),
        'random_state': RANDOM_STATE,
        'n_jobs': -1
    }
    clf = RandomForestClassifier(**params)
    clf.fit(X_train_proc, y_train)
    y_val_proba = clf.predict_proba(X_val_proc)[:,1]
    score = roc_auc_score(y_val, y_val_proba)
    return score

# Ejecutar estudio breve (puedes aumentar n_trials)
study_rf = optuna.create_study(direction='maximize', study_name='rf_study')
study_rf.optimize(rf_objective, n_trials=30, show_progress_bar=True)
print("Best RF params:", study_rf.best_params)
best_rf = RandomForestClassifier(**study_rf.best_params, random_state=RANDOM_STATE, n_jobs=-1)
best_rf.fit(X_train_proc, y_train)
joblib.dump(best_rf, ARTIFACTS_DIR / "rf_best.joblib")
print("RF guardado en", ARTIFACTS_DIR / "rf_best.joblib")

def lgb_objective(trial):
    dtrain = lgb.Dataset(X_train_proc, label=y_train)
    dvalid = lgb.Dataset(X_val_proc, label=y_val, reference=dtrain)

    param = {
        'objective': 'binary',
        'metric': 'auc',
        'verbosity': -1,
        'boosting_type': 'gbdt',
        'learning_rate': trial.suggest_float('learning_rate', 0.01, 0.2, log=True),
        'num_leaves': trial.suggest_int('num_leaves', 15, 255),
        'max_depth': trial.suggest_int('max_depth', 3, 20),
        'min_data_in_leaf': trial.suggest_int('min_data_in_leaf', 1, 100),
        'feature_fraction': trial.suggest_float('feature_fraction', 0.5, 1.0),
        'bagging_fraction': trial.suggest_float('bagging_fraction', 0.5, 1.0),
        'bagging_freq': trial.suggest_int('bagging_freq', 0, 10),
        'seed': RANDOM_STATE
    }

    gbm = lgb.train(
        param,
        dtrain,
        valid_sets=[dvalid],
        num_boost_round=200
    )

    y_val_proba = gbm.predict(X_val_proc)
    return roc_auc_score(y_val, y_val_proba)


study_lgb = optuna.create_study(direction='maximize', study_name='lgb_study')
study_lgb.optimize(lgb_objective, n_trials=30, show_progress_bar=True)

print("Best LGB params:", study_lgb.best_params)

# Entrenar con mejores params
best_lgb = lgb.LGBMClassifier(
    **study_lgb.best_params,
    objective='binary',
    n_estimators=500,
    random_state=RANDOM_STATE
)

best_lgb.fit(X_train_proc, y_train)
joblib.dump(best_lgb, ARTIFACTS_DIR / "lgb_best.joblib")
print("LGB guardado en", ARTIFACTS_DIR / "lgb_best.joblib")

def create_model(trial, input_dim):
    # sugerir hiperparmetros
    n_units1 = trial.suggest_int('n_units1', 16, 256)
    n_units2 = trial.suggest_int('n_units2', 8, 128)
    dropout_rate = trial.suggest_float('dropout_rate', 0.0, 0.5)
    lr = trial.suggest_float('lr', 1e-4, 1e-2, log=True)
    
    model = keras.Sequential([
        layers.InputLayer(input_shape=(input_dim,)),
        layers.Dense(n_units1, activation='relu'),
        layers.Dropout(dropout_rate),
        layers.Dense(n_units2, activation='relu'),
        layers.Dropout(dropout_rate),
        layers.Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')
    ])
    model.compile(optimizer=keras.optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=lr),
                  loss='binary_crossentropy',
                  metrics=['AUC'])
    return model

# Wrapper for Optuna
def keras_objective(trial):
    input_dim = X_train_proc.shape[1]
    model = create_model(trial, input_dim)
    # callbacks
    es = keras.callbacks.EarlyStopping(monitor='val_loss', patience=5, restore_best_weights=True)
    history = model.fit(
        X_train_proc, y_train,
        validation_data=(X_val_proc, y_val),
        epochs=50,
        batch_size=trial.suggest_categorical('batch_size', [32,64,128]),
        callbacks=[es],
        verbose=0
    )
    # eval
    y_val_proba = model.predict(X_val_proc).ravel()
    return roc_auc_score(y_val, y_val_proba)

study_keras = optuna.create_study(direction='maximize', study_name='keras_study')
study_keras.optimize(keras_objective, n_trials=20, show_progress_bar=True)
print("Best Keras params:", study_keras.best_params)

# Entrenar modelo final con params ptimos
best_keras_model = create_model(study_keras.best_trial, X_train_proc.shape[1])
es = keras.callbacks.EarlyStopping(monitor='val_loss', patience=5, restore_best_weights=True)
history = best_keras_model.fit(X_train_proc, y_train, validation_data=(X_val_proc, y_val), epochs=100, batch_size=study_keras.best_params.get('batch_size', 32), callbacks=[es], verbose=1)

# Guardar modelo Keras
keras_path = ARTIFACTS_DIR / "keras_model.h5"
best_keras_model.save(keras_path)
print("Keras model guardado en", keras_path)

# Guardar history para graficar
joblib.dump(history.history, ARTIFACTS_DIR / "keras_history.joblib")

## **(16) Notas sobre compatibilidad y buenas prcticas** *(resumen)*
  • Guarda preprocessor.joblib y modelos sklearn con joblib.dump para mayor compatibilidad. Evita dep-version mismatch (documenta la versin de scikit-learn). :contentReferenceoaicite:4
  • Modelos Keras: guarda con model.save('model.h5') o SavedModel. Si despliegas en otro entorno, asegrate de tener la misma versin de TensorFlow/Keras o exportar ONNX si lo prefieres. :contentReferenceoaicite:5
  • Streamlit: verifica Python 3.93.13 y define requirements.txt con versiones concretas para evitar fallos al desplegar. :contentReferenceoaicite:6
  • Serializacin: para reproducibilidad, adems del archivo del modelo guarda:
    • requirements.txt
    • environment.yml o runtime.txt (segn plataforma)
    • artifacts/metadata.json con versiones de libreras (puedes generarlo con pip freeze > artifacts/requirements.txt)
Code 
import subprocess
reqs_path = ARTIFACTS_DIR / "requirements.txt"
with open(reqs_path, "w") as f:
    subprocess.run(["pip","freeze"], stdout=f)
print("requirements.txt guardado en", reqs_path)

meta = {
    "date": datetime.utcnow().isoformat(),
    "random_state": RANDOM_STATE
}
with open(ARTIFACTS_DIR / "metadata.json", "w") as f:
    json.dump(meta, f, indent=2)
print("metadata guardada.")
